    <text n="12" corresp="#PL12F12" xml:lang="emodeng">
        <body>
            <div n="12" type="plate" facs="../images/Derricke_EUL_first_edition/EUL_plate12.jpg">
                <div type="woodcut" corresp="#PL12F12_woodcut">
                    <figure>
                        <graphic url="../images/Derricke_EUL_first_edition/EUL_plate12.tif"/>
                        <figDesc corresp="./plateNotes.xml#PL12F12_plateDesc"/>
                    </figure>
                </div>
                <div rend="blackplate" type="descriptiveText" corresp="#PL12F12_descriptiveText">
                    <div type="column" n="1" corresp="#PL12F12_column1">
                        <cb n="1"/>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="1">When flickering fame had filled the ears of marshall<!-- mods --> men of might,</l>
                            <l n="2">With rare report of <hi rend="roman"><persName corresp="#HSidney">Sidney</persName>’s</hi> praise. (that honourable knight)</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="3">And though the brute in Irish soil did well confirm the same,</l>
                            <l n="4">As who could say in <placeName corresp="#England">England</placeName>’s claim, of Justice there he came,</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="5">And to maintain the sacred right, of such a <rs corresp="#QElizabeth">Virgin Queen</rs>,</l>
                            <l n="6">For seeking of her Subject’s wealth, whose like hath never been,</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="7">The great <hi rend="roman"><persName corresp="#TONeill">O’Neill</persName></hi>, to strike the stroke, ensealing up the same,</l>  
                        </lg>
                    </div>
                    <div type="middleMargin">
                        <metamark place="middleMargin" function="plateID" corresp="#PL12F12_plateMark" rend="allcaps">12</metamark>
                        <note type="clarification">Number “12” next to the column identifies this as plate 12.</note>
                    </div>
                    <div type="column" n="2" corresp="#PL12F12_column2">
                        <cb n="2"/>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme --><!-- Need to connect this <lg> to the previous one, maybe @next and @prev? -->
                            <l n="8">And to prepare this noble knight, a way to greater fame</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="9">Amazed with such strange reports, and of his own accord,</l>
                            <l n="10">Came in prostrating him before, the presence of this Lord.</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="11">With humble suit for <rs corresp="#QElizabeth">Prince</rs>’s grace, and mercy to obtain,</l>
                            <l n="12">With like request upon the same, his friendship to attain</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="13">Who promised then by pledge of life, and virtue of his hand,</l>
                            <l n="14">Forever to <rs corresp="#QElizabeth">her noble grace</rs>, a subject true to stand,</l>
                        </lg>
                    </div>
                    <div type="column" n="3" corresp="#PL12F12_column3">
                        <cb n="3"/>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="15">And to defend in each respect, her honour and her name,</l>
                            <l n="16">Against all whose that durst deface, the glory of the same.</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="17">Which things with other actions moe,<!-- mods --> redound unto the fame</l>
                            <l n="18">Of good <hi rend="roman"><persName corresp="#HSidney">Sir Henry Sidney</persName></hi> Knight, so called by his name.</l>
                        </lg>
                        <lg type="couplet" rhyme="ADD"><!-- Add rhyme scheme -->
                            <l n="19">Lo where he sits in honour’s seat, most comely to be seen,</l>
                            <l n="20">As worthy for to represent, the person of a Queen.</l>
                        </lg>
                    </div>
                    <div type="imprint" corresp="#PL12F12_imprint">
                        <p><metamark place="margin" corresp="#PL12F12_pilcrow"/><g ref="#pilcrow">¶</g> <hi rend="roman">FINIS</hi>.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
